_meanings:
{@--1@} To roam or wander about,
move or go about, rove, ramble
(<ab>fig.</ab> also); {#Bramati Buvane kaMdarpAjYA#}  
<ls>Māl. 1. 17</ls>; {#mano nizWASUnyaM Bramati ca#} 
{#kimapyAliKati ca#} <ls n="Māl. 1.">31</ls>; <ab>oft.</ab> with <ab>acc.</ab> of
place; {#BuvaM baBrAma#} <ls>Dk.</ls>; {#digmaMqalaM Bramasi#}
{#mAnasa cApalena#} <ls>Bh. 3. 77</ls>; so {#BikzAM#}
{#Bram#} ‘to go about begging’.

{@--2@} To turn
or whirl round, revolve, move round
or in a circle; {#sUryo BrAmyati nityameva#}
{#gagane#} <ls>Bh. 2. 95</ls>; {#BramatA BramareRa#}  
<ls>Gīt. 3.</ls>

{@--4@} To spread, prevail, be
current of afloat; {#aBramacca#} 
{#pOrajAnapadezviyaM vArtA#} <ls>Dk.</ls>

{@--6@} To err, be in
error or mistake, be mistaken;  
{#ABaraRakArastu tAlavya iti baBrAma#}.

{@--2@} To cause to err,
delude, mislead, perplex, confuse,
embarrass, cause to reel or stagger;
{#vikAraScEtanyaM Bramayati ca saMmIlayati ca#}
<ls>U. 1. 36.</ls>
